Review_title: Over all I feel this product is good & Value for Money
Review_body: Starting with the build, the cool slate is well put. Although materials feels cheap, but found them sturdy. Also the two elevation levels provides for good enough raise. I used it on my office HP Pavillion Laptop & my personal ASUS TUF A15 GAMING LAPTOP which are both 15.6 inches display size.The red lighting is good, much easier to work with in the dark compared to the blue lighting which strains eyes.The fan control has two regulators one controlling the center and another controlling the other 4. They can be also switched off, which was a welcome addition.Over all I feel this product is good.

Review_title: Effective cooling, worth it for 999, ok sturdiness
Review_body: Used for Asus 15.6 inch laptop that takes in cool air from below and sends out hot air from sides.Pros:1. 5 fans adjustable (not individually). Basically, you will be keeping it at max always.2. Achieved cooling of about 15-18 degree celsius on my "overheating" laptop.3. Pad pushes cool air into the laptop from below. Useful for laptops that take in cool air from beneath and vent out hot air from sides.Cons:1. Build is decent but not that sturdy. Ok for the price.2. 1200rpm feels slow on hand but cooling was seen to be efficient still.Verdict:Steal deal for Rs. 999

Review_title: Received defective one, had to fix it. My suggestion, look for a better one than this.
Review_body: The product which I received was defective, 2 fans weren't working. Placed for refund but then thought of fixing it myself, the screws weren't fitted well had to remove the top and rearrange all the fans to fix it and it worked, so cancelled the refund. The product looks good but remember it is NOT build for gaming. The fans speed is very low, can only be used to regulate air flow below the laptop. I tried it for gaming on my Acer Predator laptop but it didn't had any impact on the temperature. Best to try other cooling pads with 2000+ RPM. Also, if you really want to lower your laptop temperature, go for thermal paste replacement, my suggestion is Arctic MX4.

Review_body: I have been looking for a laptop cooler especially for my gaming laptop and tried many products but as most of them are USB based the power  provided to the fans from the Laptop is very less and consequently the fan speed  and air flow is not good enough to cool any gaming laptop. For normal laptops these products are fine.Zinq Technologies Cool Slate Five Fan Cooling Pad: This product falls under the same category but I found it to be little better in terms of cooling due to its design and 5 Fans ,plus at this price range it is worth the money.Pros++5 Fansmetal meshing at the tops allows better air flow compared to other brands I have triedFits up-to 15.6 inch gaming laptops nothing bigger.Cons--The USB ports and cable quality is averageSuggestion : If you are into gaming use the laptop cooling pad with a  laptop vacuum cooler and it will help to keep the system cool, better than not having any.

Review_body: The product is good, but the packing was really bad. The upper metallic mesh is little delicate and when I received my order, it has a dent on it and that is why it is touching one of the fans, which further resist the fan to rotate. I solved the problem my self by just opening it and removing the dent from the mesh but I still recommend to improve the packing to prevent such issues.

Review_body: Starting with the build, the cooler is well put. Although materials feels cheap, but found them sturdy. The red lighting is a welcome, much easier to work with in the dark compared to the blue lighting.The fan control has two regulator one controlling the center and another controlling the other 4. They can be also switched off, which was a welcome addition. Also the two elevation levels provides for good enough raise.The cooling performance was more than satisfactory, was able to reduce the idle temp as much as by 8-10 degrees on an average, hence serves the purpose.

Review_title: Sturdy design. Good built and looks !
Review_body: Pretty sturdy design for its price range.. there are two rotatory controls at the back: one for the center fan abd one for the corner fans. size of all the fans seem similar though. The extra usb at the back is helpful as an aditional uabbfor pendrives/ USB mouse. Shall update on the usefulness in terms of temp reduction after few weeks of usage with various stress level on the laptop. Over all good design and materials in the price bracket
